29/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Rasim Ljajic, head of Serbia's national council for co-operation with The Hague war crimes tribunal, resigned on Tuesday (December 29th) as co-ordinator of the Action Team for locating and arresting the remaining fugitives.
Ljajic tendered his resignation to Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic, explaining fugitive Ratko Mladic, the former Bosnian Serb military commander, will not be arrested by year's end as expected.
Ljajic will remain head of the national council but will not be included in operative activities.
(Tanjug, RTS, FoNET - 29/12/09;
Beta, B92, RTS, Tanjug - 28/12/09)
